comments.comment: 5:30 Ashton Sander's outfit was on theme with the Gilded Era. It was a reference to the Buffalo Soldier uniform, which were active from the 1866-1951.  They were African American soldiers, nicknamed the "Colored Cavalry" by the Indigenous tribes during the Indian Wars at Fort Leavenworth, Kansas.  Not every reference has to be a typical go to of the time period, and I like that he went with something that showcased a part of African American history during the Gilded Era.
